  "market_context": "September 25, 2023, during New York session. Price had formed a previous high on the 15-minute chart, with an unfilled bearish fair value gap (SIBI) below it in the discount zone of the range. Analyst anticipated a liquidity sweep of the prior high followed by a move toward the FVG.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the previous 15-minute swing high (buy-side liquidity), closed down on the 5-minute chart, and created a bearish FVG on the 30-second chart—providing a high-probability short entry with tight 10-point stop and 4.22R potential to the drawn liquidity low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the 15-minute chart, identified a previous swing high that had not yet been taken out, with an unfilled bearish fair value gap (SIBI) resting below it in the discount zone of the current range.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the 5-minute chart and observed price sweeping that previous high (stop raid on buy-side liquidity), followed by a down-close candle confirming bearish delivery.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 30-second chart and located a newly formed bearish fair value gap (FVG) just below the sweep level, marking it as the entry zone.",
    "Step 4: Placed a short entry at the FVG with a 10-point stop (placed at the high of the sweep candle, not above it), targeting the prior 5-minute low for a 4.22R reward.",
    "Step 5: Noted that while the fixed 1:1 target was hit quickly, the structural target (previous low) offered significantly higher R:R and aligned with the HTF bias."
  ],
  "outcome": "TP hit at 1:1 initially; structural target (prior low) would have yielded 4.22R. Trade executed live with 10-point stop, confirmed by annotations on 1-min and 3-min charts (frames f016–f018).",
  "lessons": "Sweeping a prior high creates buy-side liquidity that smart money targets; pairing that with a newly formed FVG on LTF provides precise entries. Always assess structural targets (e.g., prior lows) for higher R:R—even if initial TP is smaller.",
